OL,3,CGuernsey Chief Minister calls for
OL,4,Cresignation of disgraced politician
OL,6,FCurrent rules stipulate he will only
OL,7,Fofficially lose his job when he is
OL,8,Fsentenced in January, but Deputy
OL,9,FLindsay de Sausmarez, head of P&R,
OL,10,Fbelieves Le Tocq should resign
OL,11,F"immediately".
OL,13,F"A resignation would be the right
OL,14,Fthing to do, so I'm strongly urging
OL,15,FJonathan Le Tocq to consider that
OL,16,Foption," Deputy de Sausmarez told ITV
OL,17,FNews.
OL,19,FShe also wants Le Tocq to pay back the
OL,20,Fmoney he has earned as a States Member
OL,21,Fsince being charged.
