OL,6,FShe clarified that while standard
OL,7,Fvetting procedures would most likely
OL,8,Fnot have flagged anything in regards
OL,9,Fto Le Tocq's case, better processes
OL,10,Fwould "enable the public to have more
OL,11,Fconfidence in the people standing for
OL,12,Felection".
OL,14,F"It is a position in which people put
OL,15,Fconsiderable trust in those
OL,16,Findividuals, and I think it is right
OL,17,Fthat we can have more confidence in
OL,18,Fthose who stand for election and are
OL,19,Fsubsequently elected.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G7/8
